CatDescriptText: Dedication stone in church reads "Tabernacle Baptist Church, organized April 29, 1874, destroyed by fire Dec. 22, 1936, rebuilt by its members in 1943, dedicated Dec. 19, 1943, Rev. L. G. McLeod, pastor."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of two men, including one wearing dark robe, possibly minister, on right, and three women, including one wearing hat with dark tulle brim and star and floral dress, standing on steps in front of Tabernacle Baptist Church, 1240 Buena Vista Street, Northside
